The above code is very inefficient for large lists. The time complexity is O(n^2). It is because we are using an if statement to check for every value in the result_list. This means that for each value in the ValuesList, we are checking the whole result_list. In the worst case, we will have to compare every value in the result_list with the current value, making the time complexity O(n^2).

This can be improved by using a set instead of a list for the result_list. A set is a data structure that stores unique elements and is much faster for checking membership.

